  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    A[External Pi Level]:::red --> B{Is External Pi Low?}:::orange\n\n    B -- \"Yes\" --> C[Pst System Activity Decreased]:::blue\n    C --> D[\\Pst System (sensor) Inactive/]:::blue\n    D --> E[PhoR (Histidine Kinase)]:::yellow\n    E --> F[PhoR Autophosphorylation]:::green\n    F --> G(\\1):::blue\n    G --> H[PhoB (Response Regulator)]:::yellow\n    G --> I[PhoR-P transfers P to PhoB]:::green\n    I --> J(\\1):::blue\n    J --> K[PhoB-P binds to Pho boxes]:::green\n    K --> L{Activation of Pho Regulon Genes}:::lavender\n    L --> M[Increased Pi Uptake Genes (e.g., Pst, Pit)]:::violet\n    L --> N[Increased Pi Scavenging Genes (e.g., PhoA, UgpB)]:::violet\n    L --> O[Increased Membrane Remodeling Genes]:::violet\n    L --> P[RpoS Induction]:::violet\n\n    M --> Q[Enhanced Pi Uptake]:::green\n    N --> S[Phosphate Scavenging]:::green\n    O --> U[Replacement of Phospholipids]:::green\n    P --> W[General Stress Response Activation]:::violet\n\n    Q --> R[Intracellular Pi from Uptake]:::blue\n    S --> T[Liberation of Pi from Organic Sources]:::blue\n    U --> V[Conservation of Intracellular Pi]:::blue\n\n    R --> AX[Intracellular Pi Pool (General)]:::blue\n    T --> AX\n    V --> AX\n    W --> X[Adaptation to Pi Starvation]:::violet\n    AX --> X\n\n    B -- \"No\" --> Y[Normal/High External Pi]:::red\n    Y --> Z[Pst System (sensor) Active]:::blue\n    Z --> AA[/Inhibition of PhoR Autophosphorylation/]:::green\n    AA --> AB[\\Pho Regulon Inactive/]:::violet\n\n    Y --> AC[High Intracellular Pi]:::blue\n    AX -- \"High Pi State\" --> AC\n    AC --> AD[Impact on PTS Phosphorylation]:::green\n    AD --> AE{Is Glucose Available?}:::orange\n    AE -- \"Yes\" --> AF[PTS Components Phosphorylated (EI-P, HPr-P, EIIA^Glc-P)]:::blue\n    AF --> AG[Sugar Uptake via PTS]:::green\n\n    AE -- \"No or High Pi\" --> AH[Accumulation of EIIA^Glc-P-free]:::blue\n    AH --> AI[Adenylate Cyclase (CyaA)]:::yellow\n    AI --> AJ[Activation of Adenylate Cyclase (CyaA)]:::green\n    AJ --> AK[ATP Input for CyaA]:::red\n    AK --> AL[CyaA converts ATP to cAMP]:::green\n    AL --> AM[Increased cAMP Levels]:::blue\n    AM --> AN[Crp (Cyclic AMP Receptor Protein)]:::yellow\n    AM --> AO[cAMP binds to Crp]:::green\n    AO --> AP[cAMP-Crp Complex]:::blue\n    AP --> AQ{Global Gene Regulation by cAMP-Crp}:::lavender\n    AQ --> AR[Activation of Carbon Catabolism Genes]:::violet\n    AQ --> AS[/Repression of Specific Stress Response Genes/]:::violet\n    AQ --> AT[Activation of Stress-mediated Death Pathway Genes]:::violet\n\n    AT --> AU[Cell Death Pathway Triggered]:::violet\n    AC --> AV[Potential Pi Toxicity]:::blue\n    AU --> AW[Reduced Cell Viability]:::violet\n    AV --> AW\n\n    AX --> BA[Synthesis of Polyphosphate (PolyP)]:::green\n    AY[ATP for PolyP Synthesis]:::red --> BA\n    AZ[Polyphosphate Kinase (PPK)]:::yellow --> BA\n    BA --> BB[PolyP Storage (Pi Reserve)]:::blue\n\n    BB --> BC[Polyphosphate Exopolyphosphatase (PPX)]:::yellow\n    BC --> BD[/Degradation of PolyP/]:::green\n    BD --> BE[Release of Intracellular Pi from PolyP]:::blue\n    BE --> AX\n\n    BF[Pyridoxal (PL)]:::red --> BI[PL + ATP -> PLP + ADP Reaction]:::green\n    BG[ATP for PLP Synthesis]:::red --> BI\n    BH[Pyridoxal Kinase]:::yellow --> BI\n    BI --> BJ[Pyridoxal 5'-Phosphate (PLP)]:::blue\n    BJ --> BK[/PLP Feedback Inhibits Pyridoxal Kinase/]:::green\n    BK --> BH\n    BJ --> BL[Regulation of PLP Levels]:::violet\n\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style B fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style R fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J